    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>Struggling Learners</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_2s0osnhy">
                <ul>
                    <li xml:id="auto_mqrcki5x"><p xml:id="auto_4zk2v6o7">Provide pre-drawn grids with mirror lines marked.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_57z6m3ym"><p xml:id="auto_us4r0uv0">Use physical mirrors to demonstrate reflection.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_g18g9e1h"><p xml:id="auto_hh6785i2">Start with <m>x</m>-axis reflections only.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_ustyf81q"><p xml:id="auto_sr1czdm1">Provide coordinate table templates.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_m0llomei"><p xml:id="auto_ogb7st7g">Pair work for support.</p></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>On-Level Learners</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_c26hroix">
                <ul>
                    <li xml:id="auto_r13njtck"><p xml:id="auto_dhkyu1pm">Complete all four problems.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_tupdrcp5"><p xml:id="auto_60xf9e6f">Work with multiple mirror lines.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_pkj7xs41"><p xml:id="auto_e6uh1lje">Verify congruence algebraically using the distance formula.</p></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>Advanced Learners</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_5n27z2wg">
                <ul>
                    <li xml:id="auto_ewfxqclq"><p xml:id="auto_82uj96os">Design a pattern with THREE mirror lines (<m>x</m>-axis, <m>y</m>-axis, and through the origin).</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_bnlvz024"><p xml:id="auto_1eyd2rc5">Investigate glide reflections.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_zyg2y4k6"><p xml:id="auto_h2t2mfzt">Analyse a real building for reflective symmetry.</p></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Extension Activities</title>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>Design Challenge</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_bjeum7hh">
                Create a symmetric garden on a <m>20\text{ m} \times 20\text{ m}</m> grid:
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_20hdo045">
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_bemf0i0i"><p xml:id="auto_fzo1n8zn">Choose at least 3 different shapes.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_77yh8a0z"><p xml:id="auto_05k6x4fd">Place them in one quadrant.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_qm12yie4"><p xml:id="auto_x4vx5nue">Reflect across both axes to create 4 copies of each shape.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_5jwvlsoe"><p xml:id="auto_cyiiu8s6">Calculate all reflected coordinates.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_x611jhtr"><p xml:id="auto_fvft3zts">Verify congruence using the distance formula.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_6gjtjg3p"><p xml:id="auto_z81bgy7n">Add a colour scheme that respects the symmetry.</p></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_ptihvnhu"><p xml:id="auto_d3q4bejs">Calculate the total area of all shapes.</p></li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_rxq2niy3">
                <alert>Bonus:</alert> Add a circular feature centred at the origin and explain why it is symmetric under all reflections.
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
    <xi:include href="../../resources-reflection.ptx"/>
</subsection>